The chemical compositions of marjoram, clary sage and anise essential oils are shown in 
 Tables 2 to 
 4. A total of 10 compounds were identified in marjoram oil by GC and GC-MS analysis (
 Table 2). Among the identified compounds, 1,8-cineole (64.61%) was the most abundant compound followed by linalool (15.28%) and 
 β–pinene (5.81%; 
 Table 2). The chemical compositions of clary sage oil showed linalayl acetate (61.16%) to be the highest concentration, followed by linalool (22.06%) and α–terpineol (4.21%; 
 Table 3). The chemical compositions of anise oil were 
 trans-anethole (82.78%), estragole (8.21%) and linalool (2.74%; 
 Table 4).
